        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:23PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 723 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bassett, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsville...
Bassett...
Axton...
Snow Creek...
Leatherwood...
Villa Heights...
and Chatmoss.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central North Carolina...and south central, southwestern and
west central Virginia.</instruction>
